-- Nigeria's Sunrise Seeks Stake in Exxon Mobil Joint Venture, FT Reports
-- Victoria Batchelor
-- 2010-06-14T23:12:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/nigeria-s-sunrise-seeks-stake-in-exxon-mobil-joint-venture-ft-reports.html

          
          
             Sunrise, a Lagos, Nigeria-based
company, has offered $4.8 billion to buy stakes in Exxon Mobil
Corp.’s oil joint venture in the African nation, the Financial
Times reported, citing people familiar with the situation that
it didn’t identify. Sunrise has made separate offers to Exxon,
which holds 40 percent of the venture, and the Nigerian
government, which holds 60 percent, and is seeking to amass a 29
percent stake, the FT said.  
